Left Sidebar (Navigation & Queues)

Top: Dashboard Icon, "All Jobs" view.

Middle (Queue List): A vertical list of your named queues (Default, HighPriority, etc.).

Micro-interaction: Each queue item shows a small badge: [Priority: 10] | [3 Pending].

Bottom: System Status footer (Scheduler Running/Idle green dot).

Top Header (Global Controls)

Left: Breadcrumbs (e.g., Home > HighPriority Queue).

Right: "Panic Button" (Red, prominent), Refresh, and Theme Toggle.

Main Content Area (Job Feed)

A dense Data Table (React Table / TanStack).

Columns: ID, Type, Target, Queue, State, Progress.

Feature: Hovering over a row reveals the context-sensitive actions (Pause, Stop, Retry).

Right Panel (The "Inspector")

Clicking a job in the main table opens this panel.

Top: Large Progress bar & Speedometer for the selected job.

Middle: "Technical Metadata" (Logs, Engine Config JSON tree).

Bottom: "Job Control Actions" (Big buttons: Restart, Archive).